# Build Notes

> **Before rebuilding:** Rename `iso-gnome.toml` or `iso-kde.toml` to `iso.toml`, commit the change, then rebuild the image.


## Local Build

### Prerequisites

| Resource | Requirement |
|---|---|
| VM Image | Fedora Workstation |
| RAM | 8192 MB |
| Disk Space | 80 GB |
| Secure Boot | **Disabled** (Settings → Security) |



### Setup

sudo dnf update -y
git clone https://github.com/zappelfryx/ZotacZoneHandheld-Bazzite.git
cd ZotacZoneHandheld-Bazzite
# To update later:
# git pull


### Build & Generate ISO (from Remote Registry)

# Build the container image
podman build -t localhost ZotacZoneHandheld-Bazzite

# Create output directory
mkdir ~/iso-output

# Generate ISO
sudo podman run --rm -it --privileged \
  -v /var/lib/containers/storage:/var/lib/containers/storage \
  -v ~/iso-output:/build/iso \
  ghcr.io/jasonn3/build-container-installer:latest \
  IMAGE_REPO=ghcr.io/zappelfryx \
  IMAGE_NAME=zotaczonehandheld-bazzite \
  IMAGE_TAG=latest \
  VERSION=41 \
  VARIANT=Kinoite

### — Build & Generate ISO (Fully Local) —
 Use this method to build and serve the image  entirely from your local machine.


# 1. Build the image locally

cd ZotacZoneHandheld-Bazzite
podman build -t localhost/zotac-zone:latest .

# 2. Start a temporary local registry

podman run -d -p 5000:5000 --name local-registry docker.io/library/registry:2

# 3. Tag and push the image to the local registry

podman tag localhost/zotac-zone:latest localhost:5000/zotac-zone:latest
podman push --tls-verify=false localhost:5000/zotac-zone:latest

# 4. Generate ISO from local registry 

sudo podman run --rm -it --privileged \
  --network=host \
  -v /var/lib/containers/storage:/var/lib/containers/storage \
  -v ~/iso-output:/build/iso \
  ghcr.io/jasonn3/build-container-installer:latest \
  IMAGE_REPO=localhost:5000 \
  IMAGE_NAME=zotac-zone \
  IMAGE_TAG=latest \
  VERSION=41 \
  VARIANT=Kinoite

# 5. Clean up local registry
podman rm -f local-registry


